NAME
  CATALOG - Stream directory contents (External)

SYNOPSIS
  CATALOG [path]

DESCRIPTION
  Lists files and subdirectories in
  the specified path using a streaming
  protocol. Unlike DIR, it is not
  limited by memory buffers and can
  list directories of any size.

EXAMPLES
  CATALOG
  CATALOG /USR/LIB

NOTES
  Use this command if DIR fails or
  truncates output due to directory
  size.

SEE ALSO
  DIR, LS, TREE